{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GuhTsNrFNzovcvMDU1d7rA","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Retrospective — 2026-03-25\n     2→\n     3→**Sprint:** Operational Excellence (Epic 13-14 — AgentDriver + Retro Pipeline)\n     4→**Session:** 10 (continuation from session 9 on 2026-03-24)\n     5→**Session window:** ~2026-03-24 20:14 UTC to ~2026-03-25 02:05 UTC (~6 hours)\n     6→\n     7→---\n     8→\n     9→## 1. Session Summary\n    10→\n    11→| Story | Epic | Outcome | Pipeline Stages | Commit Time |\n    12→|-------|------|---------|-----------------|-------------|\n    13→| 13-1-agentdriver-interface-and-types | Epic 13 (AgentDriver) | done | create-story, dev-story, code-review, verification | 2026-03-24 20:14 |\n    14→| 13-2-ralph-driver-implementation | Epic 13 (AgentDriver) | done | create-story, dev-story, code-review, verification | 2026-03-24 20:14 |\n    15→| 13-3-migrate-run-ts-to-agentdriver | Epic 13 (AgentDriver) | done | create-story, dev-story, code-review, verification | 2026-03-24 20:37 |\n    16→| 14-1-retro-to-sprint-pipeline-epic-td | Epic 14 (Tech Debt Pipeline) | done | create-story, dev-story, code-review, verification | 2026-03-25 02:05 |\n    17→\n    18→**Net progress:** Epic 13 fully closed (all 3 stories done). Epic 14 started — 1 of 7 stories done, 6 remain in backlog. Overall sprint: 54 of 66 stories done (82%).\n    19→\n    20→All four stories passed the full pipeline: story creation, development, adversarial code review, and verification. No story required retry.\n    21→\n    22→---\n    23→\n    24→## 2. Issues Analysis\n    25→\n    26→### Bugs Discovered During Implementation or Verification\n    27→\n    28→| Severity | Story | Issue | Fixed? |\n    29→|----------|-------|-------|--------|\n    30→| HIGH | 14-1 | `generateSlug('')` returned `''`, creating malformed TD story keys like `TD-1-` | Yes |\n    31→| HIGH | 14-1 | `backlogAppended` reported items as persisted when `projectRoot` was omitted — misleading return value | Yes |\n    32→| HIGH | 14-1 | `wordOverlap` exceeded 1.0 with duplicate words in input, breaking the 0-1 dedup contract | Yes |\n    33→| MEDIUM | 14-1 | Missing test for no-projectRoot code path in backlog append | Yes |\n    34→\n    35→Code review caught 3 HIGH bugs and 1 MEDIUM gap in story 14-1. All fixed in the same review cycle. The `wordOverlap > 1.0` bug was a set-vs-array issue — using `new Set()` for deduplication resolved it.\n    36→\n    37→### Workarounds Applied (Tech Debt Introduced)\n    38→\n    39→1. **`getExistingTdTitles` reconstructs titles from slugs** (14-1, LOW, not fixed) — Slug-to-title reverse mapping loses fidelity (hyphens could be spaces or original hyphens). Acceptable for dedup threshold matching but not exact comparisons.\n    40→2. **`createTdStory` implicitly creates `epic-TD` via spread+override** (14-1, LOW, not fixed) — Does not call `ensureEpicTd()` explicitly, relying on caller to have done so. Works but fragile if called directly.\n    41→\n    42→### Code Quality Concerns\n    43→\n    44→1. **`state.ts` at 543 lines** — exceeds the 300-line limit (NFR5). Pre-existing from before this session. The epic-TD override was a minimal 2-line addition to `generateSprintStatusYaml()`, so the story did not meaningfully worsen it.\n    45→2. **`sprint-yaml.test.ts` at 388 lines** — also over the limit. Pre-existing.\n    46→3. **No test for `appendToBacklogFile` append-to-existing path or error handling** — Coverage gap noted by code review. The happy path (create new file) is tested; the append and error paths are not.\n    47→\n    48→### Verification Gaps\n    49→\n    50→None significant. All 10 ACs for story 14-1 passed unit-testable verification with direct CLI checks. No ACs were escalated or given weak evidence."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_012gKToCM6uACCLJ7JKa3R8g","session_id":"c7000265-a715-4aee-b7e2-8633daa4e5a3","uuid":"979b0e93-e53e-49a2-bfbb-534dbcce1075","times