{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016EfVXnqpfRwDTT5c3Xsnk5","type":"tool_result","content":"  2700→- **Wasted session ratio for the day:** 11/17 sessions (64.7%) were no-ops\n  2701→\n  2702→---\n  2703→\n  2704→## 5. Lessons Learned\n  2705→\n  2706→1. **Circuit breakers must measure outcomes, not activity.** Checking \"did files change\" is insufficient — ralph's own bookkeeping files always change. The check must be \"did a story transition to a new status\" or \"were any commits created.\"\n  2707→2. **Consecutive NO_WORK needs a hard cap.** After 2-3 consecutive NO_WORK results, ralph should terminate the loop and report to the user rather than continuing to spawn sessions.\n  2708→3. **Retry-exhausted + flagged should signal sprint completion.** When all non-done stories are flagged/retry-exhausted, the sprint is \"effectively complete\" and ralph should exit with a clear summary rather than looping.\n  2709→4. **Subagent feedback needs an upward channel.** Subagents correctly diagnosed the problem from session 8 onward, but their observations in `.session-issues.md` were never read by the loop controller.\n  2710→\n  2711→---\n  2712→\n  2713→## 6. Action Items\n  2714→\n  2715→| Priority | Action | Owner |\n  2716→|----------|--------|-------|\n  2717→| P0 | Add consecutive NO_WORK counter to ralph loop — terminate after 3 consecutive no-ops | Dev (ralph/ralph.sh or equivalent) |\n  2718→| P0 | Fix circuit breaker to check story status transitions, not file modification timestamps | Dev (ralph/.circuit_breaker_state logic) |\n  2719→| P1 | Add \"effectively complete\" detection: if all non-done stories are flagged/retry-exhausted, exit loop with summary | Dev (ralph) |\n  2720→| P1 | Resolve 14-4-observability-backend-choice: either descope, redesign as unit-testable, or run manually with Docker access | Human / PM |\n  2721→| P2 | Add subagent-to-controller feedback channel so ralph can read NO_WORK signals from its own subagents | Dev (ralph) |\n  2722→| P2 | Add API credit tracking/estimation to ralph to surface cost of no-op sessions | Dev (ralph) |\n  2723→\n  2724→---\n  2725→\n  2726→## Updated End-of-Day Sprint Summary — 2026-03-25 (Final, Session 17)\n  2727→\n  2728→| Metric | Value |\n  2729→|--------|-------|\n  2730→| Stories completed | 65/66 (98.5%) |\n  2731→| Epics completed | 15/16 (Epic 14 has 1 story remaining) |\n  2732→| Stories completed today | 10 (sessions 1-6) |\n  2733→| Total sessions today | 17 (loops 1-17) |\n  2734→| Productive sessions | 6 (sessions 1-6) |\n  2735→| No-op sessions | 11 (sessions 7-17) |\n  2736→| Wasted session ratio | 64.7% (11/17) |\n  2737→| Remaining blocker | 14-4-observability-backend-choice (Docker keychain, retry-exhausted, 10/10) |\n  2738→| Circuit breaker status | BROKEN — does not detect no-ops (monitors file changes, not work outcomes) |\n  2739→| Test suite | 3799 tests passing, 97.1% coverage |\n  2740→| Critical fix needed | Ralph consecutive-no-op termination + circuit breaker outcome-based detection |\n  2741→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_012gKToCM6uACCLJ7JKa3R8g","session_id":"c7000265-a715-4aee-b7e2-8633daa4e5a3","uuid":"15843038-2f24-418b-a511-5a08b26dd046","timestamp":"2026-03-25T07:48:32.917Z"}
